  28:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c **** /*++
  29:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c **** 
  30:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c **** Routine Description:
  31:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c **** 
  32:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c ****     Initialize a basic mutual exclusion lock.   Each lock
  33:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c ****     provides mutual exclusion access at it's task priority
  34:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c ****     level.  Since there is no-premption (at any TPL) or
  35:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c ****     multiprocessor support, acquiring the lock only consists
  36:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c ****     of raising to the locks TPL.
  37:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c **** 
  38:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c ****     Note on a debug build the lock is acquired and released
  39:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c ****     to help ensure proper usage.
  40:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c ****     
  41:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c **** Arguments:
  42:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c **** 
  43:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c ****     Lock        - The FLOCK structure to initialize
  44:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c **** 
  45:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c ****     Priority    - The task priority level of the lock
  46:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c **** 
  47:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c ****     
  48:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c **** Returns:
  49:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c **** 
  50:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c ****     An initialized F Lock structure.
  51:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c **** 
  52:../Backend/gnu-efi-3.0.9/lib/lock.c **** --*/
